<div id="review_2969652851" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2969652851" />
    <a title="Shafay Ishtiaq" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/95457148-shafay-ishtiaq"><img alt="Shafay Ishtiaq" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1570093519p2/95457148.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2969652851?book_show_action=true">Sep 27, 2019</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Shafay Ishtiaq" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Shafay Ishtiaq" href="/user/show/95457148-shafay-ishtiaq">Shafay Ishtiaq</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/95457148-shafay-ishtiaq?shelf=fiction">fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2969652851" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer8317753505195808753"><blockquote> <b> “Out beyond ideas<br/>of wrongdoing and right doing,<br/>there is a field.<br/>I’ll meet you there.” </b> </blockquote><br/><br/><i> ‘And the Mountains Echoed’ </i> is the third book of <i> Khalid Hosseini </i> which I have read and he is definitely up there as one of my favorite writers. <i> Khalid </i> is an amazing story teller and uses simple words to describe people and surroundings which is quite effective.<br/><br/>The book is written in a different style from the previous two books of <i> Khalid </i> . The book contains different chapters and each chapter is told </span>
  <span id="freeText8317753505195808753" style="display:none"><blockquote> <b> “Out beyond ideas<br />of wrongdoing and right doing,<br />there is a field.<br />I’ll meet you there.” </b> </blockquote><br /><br /><i> ‘And the Mountains Echoed’ </i> is the third book of <i> Khalid Hosseini </i> which I have read and he is definitely up there as one of my favorite writers. <i> Khalid </i> is an amazing story teller and uses simple words to describe people and surroundings which is quite effective.<br /><br />The book is written in a different style from the previous two books of <i> Khalid </i> . The book contains different chapters and each chapter is told from the perspective of a different character. The main focus of the story is the life of one family and the story of life of people that are linked with this family. Stories of most characters were good but few characters stories seemed a little dragged. The novel stretches over a long period from 1952 to 2010.<br /><br />The story is touching, emotional, heartbreaking and talks about the hardship of the lives of the people. How everyone have to take tough decisions and make sacrifices which not only affects their lives but also of people close to them. <br /><br /><blockquote> <b> “I learned that the world didn't see the inside of you, that it didn't care a whit about the hopes and dreams, and sorrows, that lay masked by skin and bone. It was as simple, as absurd, and as cruel as that.” </b> </blockquote><br /><br /><blockquote> <b> “All good things in life are fragile and easily lost” </b> </blockquote><br /><br />Overall, it was a good reading. I was hooked on to it and enjoyed every moment of reading it. :)<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="8317753505195808753" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


